its an hello world programme

Console.WriteLine("Hello Priyanshu"),

for assigning variable .....

string aFriend = ", how are you";
Console.WriteLine(aFriend);

adding string with a variable

string aFriend = "Bill";
Console.WriteLine("hello" + aFriend);

shortcut for the above code is an 

Console.WriteLine($"Hello Priyanshu{aFriend}"

work with strings

for more friends

string firstFriend = "Priyanshu";
string secondFriend = "sachin";
Console.WriteLine($"My friends are {firstFriend} and {secondFriend}");

calculating the length of a strings.....

Console.WriteLine($"The name {firstFriend} has {firstFriend.Length} letters.");
Console.WriteLine($"The name {secondFriend} has {secondFriend.Length} letters.");

sometime strings have leading and trailing spaces.....

string greeting = "      Hello World!       ";
Console.WriteLine($"[{greeting}]");

for an converting a 

string trimmedGreeting = greeting.TrimStart();
Console.WriteLine($"[{trimmedGreeting}]");

trimmedGreeting = greeting.TrimEnd();
Console.WriteLine($"[{trimmedGreeting}]");

trimmedGreeting = greeting.Trim();
Console.WriteLine($"[{trimmedGreeting}]");

output:
[      Hello World!       ]
[Hello World!       ]
[      Hello World!]
[Hello World!]

explanation......
here we are seeing that the .trimstart trimed strting part and .trimend trimed ending part
while .trimed all start and end backspaces.... 

now here we learn how to replaced a string....

input:
string sayHello = "Hello World!";
Console.WriteLine(sayHello);
sayHello = sayHello.Replace("Hello", "Greetings");
Console.WriteLine(sayHello);

output;
Hello World!
Greetings World!

so here simple things got replaced....

for here converting a string in to in upper and lowercase
you do 
input:
Console.WriteLine(sayHello.ToUpper());
Console.WriteLine(sayHello.ToLower());
output:
GREETINGS WORLD!
greetings world!

so here you saw changes

#searching strings

input:
string songLyrics = "You say goodbye, and I say hello";
Console.WriteLine(songLyrics.Contains("goodbye"));
Console.WriteLine(songLyrics.Contains("greetings"));
output:
True
False
